<br>
   You're saying that the people who <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> can</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> already do what they want (roleplay) on an existing server would be more likely to move than the people who <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> can't</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Get unique items, some named after you, get a baseball card like webpage tracking your characters stats n such, etc)???<br>
<br>
   W...t....f...?<br>
<br>
   Again, I'm not saying Legends would be un-fun.  But you have to be smoking some <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> serious</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> crack if you think they're targetting the roleplaying audience.  Dynamic content does not equal roleplaying.  Remember when they had those shady citizens and stuff in Qeynos?  That was dynamic content.  They added new textures (huts n such), and all these creepy guys were around.  Was there more roleplaying?  No.  You had a bunch of dorky casters all out there screaming at eachother over who had the rights to the camps so they could get a damask robe before the quest played itself out.<br>
<br>
   If you want to move your guild there and attempt to start a roleplaying community, feel free, but you've gotta be drunk to think that you're going to somehow find a more receptive community than you would on Firiona Vie.<br>
